<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.foolscourt.com/images/sig.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=courtjester@teamskald>CourtJester</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#ff0000>(9/22/03 12:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=704.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> depends</span><hr size=1> Well, I guess it depends on individual playstyle and on how RvR looks on your server.<br>
On Guinevere, it's all about elite. The group who wins is usually the group who mezzes 1st, pick the right targets and assist. I don't see any reason to have AP for a Skald unless you go solo sometimes, since in group I usually have 2 savages, a zerk and warrior behind me hitting the same target with celerity 3 and up.<br>
Even solo, you'll have to be lucky to get any kill. Having stealther groups hanging around the g2 in Emain during midweek daytime make the life of the lone wolves pretty hard.<br>
<br>
AP/AoF are  waay to costy RAs for the profit they bring. Not that IP is cheap, but what makes the big difference is the fact that AP/AoF lets you avoid % of the MELEE hits you take, and melee alone, while IP is useful for every situation. And even if it doesn't save you, it can let you live a little bit longer, survive a few more nukes and get a few more RP's.<br>
<br>
I did a calculation once of the approx damage I take in a standard battle from melee and from spells.... I think it ended up with 85% for spells 15% melee. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=courtjester@teamskald>CourtJester</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#ff0000>(9/22/03 12:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=704.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ehhh</span><hr size=1> Sorry, i vote for IP of course. It won't let me vote for some reason. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=elvana@teamskald>Elvana</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 31<br> <font color=#ff0000>(9/22/03 2:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=704.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ehhh</span><hr size=1> At 6l5 im going to probably respec to:<br>
